# {{.RepoName}}

`{{.RepoName}}` is a [Terraform](https://www.terraform.io) provider for the
`{{.Name}}` service, built on the open-core
[devedge-terraform-sdk](https://github.com/infobloxopen/devedge-terraform-sdk)
`tfkit` runtime. It is the Terraform mirror of a devedge CLI: a small
hand-written seam (`internal/provider/provider.go`) composes the reusable tfkit
provider base with **generated resource modules**, one per API resource,
produced by `de terraform add`.

Registry address: `registry.terraform.io/{{.Org}}/{{.Name}}`.

## Layout

- `main.go` — serves the provider (`providerserver.Serve`).
- `internal/provider/provider.go` — the hand-written seam: it wires the tfkit
  base (endpoint/token config + shared client) and registers the generated
  resources. **Owned by you**; `de terraform add` never overwrites it.
- `internal/provider/resources_gen.go` — generated registration of all
  resources. Rewritten by `de terraform add`; do not edit.
- `internal/provider/<resource>_resource.go`, `<resource>_resource_gen.go`,
  `provider_code_spec.json` — one generated resource module per API resource.
  Generated by tfgen through `de terraform add`; do not edit.

## Add a resource

Generate a resource from an enriched OpenAPI v3 spec and wire it into the
provider:

```
de terraform add --input path/to/service.openapi.yaml --resource widget
go mod tidy
go build ./...
```

Re-running `de terraform add` for a resource regenerates it in place;
`resources_gen.go` is rewritten to register every resource under
`internal/provider/`.

## Configure and use

Configure the provider with the service endpoint and a bearer token, either in
the provider block or via the `{{.EnvPrefix}}_ENDPOINT` and `{{.EnvPrefix}}_TOKEN`
environment variables:

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    {{.Name}} = {
      source = "{{.Org}}/{{.Name}}"
    }
  }
}

provider "{{.Name}}" {
  endpoint = "https://api.example.com"
  # token   = "..."   # or set {{.EnvPrefix}}_TOKEN
}

resource "{{.Name}}_widget" "example" {
  # attributes generated from the API resource
}
```

## Build locally

```
go mod tidy
go build ./...
```

To use a local build with Terraform, add a `dev_overrides` block to your
Terraform CLI config (`~/.terraformrc`) pointing `{{.Org}}/{{.Name}}` at the
directory holding the built binary. See the Terraform docs on provider
development overrides.

## Publish to the Terraform Registry

Releases are cut by [GoReleaser](https://goreleaser.com) on a `v*` tag
(`.github/workflows/release.yml`), following the HashiCorp provider release
shape: zip archives, a GPG-detached-signed `SHA256SUMS`, and
`terraform-registry-manifest.json` published alongside them.

One-time setup:

1. Generate a GPG signing key and add its **public** key to your Terraform
   Registry account.
2. Add two repository secrets:
   - `GPG_PRIVATE_KEY` — the ASCII-armored private key
     (`gpg --armor --export-secret-keys <key-id>`).
   - `PASSPHRASE` — the key's passphrase.
3. Publish the provider on the Terraform Registry and connect this repository.

Then push a semver tag to cut a release:

```
git tag v0.1.0
git push origin v0.1.0
```

To verify the build without any signing credentials:

```
goreleaser build --snapshot --clean
```

## Documentation

Provider and resource docs live under `docs/` (generate them with
[`tfplugindocs`](https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform-plugin-docs)). The
Registry serves whatever is committed there.
